{
  "texts": [
    "Many risks are caused by accidents [4,14] or the misuse of specific AI systems [6,33,60].",
    "In both cases, the deployment decision is a decisive moment.",
    "Ideally, companies should discover potential failure modes and vulnerabilities before they deploy a system, and stop the deployment process if they cannot reduce risks to an acceptable level.",
    "But not all risks are caused by the deployment of individual models.",
    "Some risks also stem from the publication of research, as research findings can be misused [6,33,60,156,169]."
  ]
}